---
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ProjectCard from "../components/ProjectCard.astro";
import SectionHeading from "../components/SectionHeading.astro";
import { getFeaturedProjects } from "../lib/projects";

const featuredProjects = getFeaturedProjects(await getCollection("projects"));
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section class="hero container section-xl">
    <div class="hero-image-wrap">
      <picture>
        <source srcset="/images/headshot-480.webp 480w, /images/headshot-960.webp 960w" type="image/webp" />
        <img
          src="/images/headshot.jpg"
          alt="Portrait of Rishav Roy at sunset"
          class="hero-image"
          width="960"
          height="1440"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </picture>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">UW–Madison B.S., ‘26 · Economics · Mathematics · Data Science</p>
      <h1>Rishav Roy</h1>
      <p class="hero-contact">Contact: roybrishav [at] gmail [dot] com</p>
      <p class="hero-identity">
        Triple major with top scores in PhD-level economics. Building the toolkit needed to study pressing issues in policy design, institutional design, and econometric/ML applications.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="#story">My Story</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="#current-projects">Current Projects</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="#interests">My Interests</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="story" class="container section story-section">
    <SectionHeading eyebrow="My Story" />
    <div class="story-prose">
      <h2 class="story-lead">
        In just three academic years, I began and completed three majors in Economics, Mathematics, and Data Science.
      </h2>
      <p class="story-statement">
        In just two academic years, I outscored all students in multiple PhD-level economics and master’s-level mathematics courses, earning a 3.9 GPA over the same period in which I completed all first-year Economics PhD courses plus 18 undergraduate-level courses.
      </p>
      <p>
        And all this after a year spent working full-time as a restaurant manager, studying part-time at a community college, and recovering from family and health issues. It is accomplishments like this that testify to how well I, in the milieu of high-stakes work, in settings both intellectually rigorous and breakneck, am able to thrive.
      </p>
      <p>
        I pride myself on being a lifelong learner—on my motivation and curiosity and ability to ask penetrating, creative questions. But it is only when combined with exceptional critical thinking abilities, advanced communication skills, and deep scientific understanding that this mixture can create potent, novel research. And it is precisely this combination that I look forward to applying in my work alongside you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="current-projects" class="container section">
    <SectionHeading eyebrow="My Current Projects" title="Research questions I am actively developing">
      <p>All of my projects can be found on the <a href="/research/">Research page</a>.</p>
    </SectionHeading>
    <div class="card-grid">
      {featuredProjects.map((project) => <ProjectCard project={project} />)}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="interests" class="container section">
    <SectionHeading eyebrow="My Interests" title="From incentives to institutions, beliefs to behaviors">
      <p>
        As the diversity of my <a href="/research/">Research</a> and <a href="/courses/">Courses</a> reflects, I am fascinated by (and trained in) many different fields.
      </p>
      <p>
        Eventually, however, I hope to apply the methods and metaphors I’ve learned to one, seemingly fixed point among my interests: the conditions under which the policies, institutions, beliefs, and behaviors needed to align private incentives with social welfare even evolve. Or, more broadly:
      </p>
    </SectionHeading>
    <div class="interest-grid">
      <article class="interest-item">
        <h3>Applied economics and policy</h3>
        <p>How do markets, institutions, and public policy shape (and get shaped by) economic opportunity, decision-making, and outcomes?</p>
      </article>
      <article class="interest-item">
        <h3>Measurement and empirical methods</h3>
        <p>How can econometrics, machine learning, and causal inference help us wring empirically falsifiable claims out of complex social questions?</p>
      </article>
      <article class="interest-item">
        <h3>Political economy of growth and welfare</h3>
        <p>How do institutional design, state capacity, and elite power shape (and get shaped by) growth, inequality, innovation, and structural transformation?</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
